Path: `.gitignore`

```gitignore
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Python / virtualenv
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.venv/
venv/
ENV/
env/
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.pyd
*.pyo
*.so
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.coverage
coverage.xml
htmlcov/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OS / editor
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Secrets / env
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Django
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
db.sqlite3
db.sqlite3-journal
*.log
staticfiles/
media/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Training outputs / artefacts (generated)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
artefacts/
*.joblib
*.pkl
*.pickle

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local datasets (keep only the tiny sample under version control)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
data/*
!data/sample_transactions.csv
!data/.gitkeep

# If you ever add dataset folders, keep them ignored by default
**/datasets/
**/raw_data/
**/real_data/
**/*paysim*
**/*creditcard*
**/*fraud*

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Notebooks (optional)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.ipynb_checkpoints/
notebooks/.ipynb_checkpoints/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Docker local volumes (if you bind-mount named dirs)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
pgdata/
postgres-data/
```

If you want `data/` to never be empty (even if you remove the sample later), add a `data/.gitkeep` file (the ignore rules above already allow it).
